  "description": "A polynomial is an expression built from a variable and constants using only addition, subtraction, and multiplication — no division by the variable, no square roots, no infinite series. The expression 3x2−5x+13x^2 - 5x + 1 is a polynomial. So is x7+2x3−xx^7 + 2x^3 - x. The constant 4 is also a polynomial (of degree zero). What makes polynomials special is their simplicity: they are the most basic expressions you can write down using algebraic operations, and yet they are rich enough to encode deep mathematical structure.\n",
